&lt;p&gt;pi-btaudio is a suite of packages that allow your RPi to connect to UE Boom automatically, and make sure the connection stays active.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start by going over the &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener external&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;bablokb&#x2F;pi-btaudio#prerequisites&quot;&gt;prerequisites&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;, make sure to write down the MAC address of your UE Boom. In order to connect to a UE Boom, you must press its Bluetooth pairing button for it to accept new connections.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once youâ€™re done, follow &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener external&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;bablokb&#x2F;pi-btaudio#installation&quot;&gt;their installation steps&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; to install the tools. Edit the configuration file in &lt;code&gt;&#x2F;etc&#x2F;asound.conf&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; with the following content (&lt;strong&gt;make sure you replace &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;UE Boom Bluetooth MAC&amp;gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; with the one found during prerequisites&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;):&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo&quot; style=&quot;color: #E1E4E8; background-color: #24292E;&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;plain&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pcm.!default &amp;quot;bluealsa&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
