&lt;p&gt;Spotcast enables Home Assistant to play music on Spotify Connect-enabled devices, like our Raspotify system. Follow the &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener external&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;fondberg&#x2F;spotcast#installation&quot;&gt;installation steps&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; to install on your Home Assistant instance. After installing, you need to configure Home Assistant to authenticate using your Spotify Premium account by following the &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener external&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;fondberg&#x2F;spotcast#configuration&quot;&gt;configuration steps&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After restarting Home Assistant, youâ€™ll be able to use Spotcast to play music on your speaker through Raspotify by calling this Home Assistant service (&lt;strong&gt;replace &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;Speaker Name&amp;gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; with what you specified in &lt;code&gt;&#x2F;etc&#x2F;default&#x2F;raspotify&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;Spotify Playlist URI&amp;gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; with the Spotify-formatted URI such as &lt;code&gt;spotify:album:2PPfl28ysMbOkl2DBJ5Dr4&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; - a good rainforest nature album&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;):&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo&quot; style=&quot;color: #E1E4E8; background-color: #24292E;&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;yaml&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #85E89D;&quot;&gt;data&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;:&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
